Rule: Higher education levels (Doctorate, Prof-school, Bachelors) significantly increase the likelihood of earning more than $50k a year.
Certain occupations, such as Service, are associated with higher income compared to Blue-Collar jobs.
Working in the Government sector may increase the likelihood of earning more than $50k a year compared to working in the Private sector.
Older individuals (e.g., those in their 30s and 50s) are more likely to earn more than $50k a year than younger individuals.
While full-time work (40 hours per week) is common, part-time work in specific high-skill professions can also lead to higher income.
